Add a database connection for use in pipe or pre-canned actions.
s3 Add an AWS S3 bucket
Use "hp config connections add [command] --help" for more information about a command.
Add an Oracle connection to the config store '/Users/richardlloyd/.halfpipe'.
Provide a DSN or supply individual flags.
Environment variables are also read where flags are missing.
By default, prefetch_rows=500 is added to parameters unless overridden.
The DSN takes presidence and should be of the form:
-c, --connection-name string Connection name referred to by pipe actions
-d, --dsn string Oracle connect string to parse (takes priority over individual flags)
-u, --user string Username or schema to connect
-D, --database-name string Database SID or service name registered with the listener
hp config connections add oracle -c myTestConnection -d user/password@myhost:1521/dbServiceName
hp config connections add oracle -c myTestConnection -d user/password@myhost:1521/dbServiceName
hp config connections add oracle -c myTestConnection -d user/password@myhost:1521/dbServiceName
Add a Snowflake connection to the config store '/Users/richardlloyd/.halfpipe'.
Either provide a DSN or supply individual flags.
-d, --dsn string Snowflake connect string to parse (this takes priority over individual flags)
-s, --schema string Schema name (omit to use default)
-D, --database-name string Database name (omit to use default)
-w, --warehouse string Snowflake compute warehouse name (omit to use default)
hp config connections add snowflake -c myTestSnowflake -d 'user:password@ea12345.eu-west-1/myDatabase?schema=mySche
hp config connections add snowflake -c myTestSnowflake -d 'user:password@ea12345.eu-west-1/myDatabase?schema=mySche

Add an AWS S3 bucket to the config store '/Users/richardlloyd/.halfpipe'.
Provide a URL or supply individual flags.
Trailing slashes are trimmed and cleaned up internally.
The URL takes presidence and should be of the form:
-d, --dsn string DSN of the form s3://<bucket name>/<prefix> (takes priority over individual flags)
hp config connections add s3 -c myDataLake -d s3://my-data-lake/my-prefix
hp config connections add s3 -c myDataLake -d s3://my-data-lake/my-prefix
hp config connections add s3 -c myDataLake -d s3://my-data-lake/my-prefix
